        <briefdescription>
<para>Compute generalized accelerations from applied efforts. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Solves forward dynamics <computeroutput>qdd = H^{-1}(tau - C)</computeroutput>.</para>
<para>Solves qdd = H(q)^-1 * (tau - C(q, qd)), where C is obtained from inverse dynamics with zero acceleration.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">model</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para><ref refid="structnovaphy_1_1_articulation" kindref="compound">Articulation</ref> graph and inertial properties. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">q</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Generalized positions. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">qd</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Generalized velocities. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">tau</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Applied joint efforts (torques/forces). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">gravity</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Gravity vector in world frame (m/s^2). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">f_ext</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Optional external spatial forces per link in link-local frame (N, N*m). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Generalized acceleration vector qdd.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>This API is commonly used for simulation stepping and inverse-control validation.</para>
</simplesect>
